{
  "texts": [
    "We generate from AMR-to-English using the English MonoQL.",
    "Then we translate that output into the target languages with the same model used to generate our silver data (4-bit quantized NLLB-3.3B).",
    "We expect this model to mirror the uneven quality of machine translation models, performing well in HR but less well in LR languages.",
    "Following NLLB Team et al. (2022), we use BLEU, a simple surface-based metric that does not rely on training data, which is an advantage when dealing with multiple languages, particularly lowresource ones.",
    "We compute the scores with Sacre-BLEU (Post, 2018) 10 and the default settings (including 13a tokenizer) for comparability with previous works."
  ]
}